  "summary": {
    "macroSummary": "Iran's declaration that the Strait of Hormuz is open and a potential uranium enrichment deal with Trump has triggered a massive risk-on move, with oil crashing below $90, bonds rallying (10Y at 4-week lows), and the dollar hitting February lows. Bitcoin surged past $78K as geopolitical risk premiums collapsed, while equities rallied hard across all indices with small caps outperforming.",
    "regimeImpact": "This geopolitical resolution removes the stagflation threat (oil sub-$100) and creates conditions for the relief rally to extend further, potentially challenging our bear market thesis if it sustains above key technical levels.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Aggressively roll BMNR cash-secured puts higher as BTC cleared $78K resistance - structural upside now likely to $80K weekend target",
      "Reduce short book exposure immediately as risk-on sentiment and geopolitical resolution could fuel sustained rally",
      "Consider rotating from Maturity overweight into Young Growth/High Growth as lower oil prices and bond yields favor growth sectors"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Oil sub-$90 eliminates stagflation risk and supports growth narrative with Fed potentially on hold rather than hiking",
      "10Y yields at 4-week lows and dollar at February lows signal major risk appetite shift that could challenge bear market regime",
      "Bitcoin's $78K breakout with crypto fear/greed at July highs suggests institutional flows returning to risk assets",
      "All equity indices up 1.3-2.3% with Russell 2000 leading indicates broad-based risk-on rotation favoring cyclicals and growth"
    ]
